    "last_activity_date" : 1466146259,
    "creation_date" : 1466146259,
    "answer_id" : 37874948,
    "question_id" : 4830253,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<blockquote>\n  <p>keytool it's a binary file into the JDK folder ... just add your JDK\n  as environment variable by adding the following line</p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<pre><code>C:\\Program Files\\Java\\jdk1.8.0_65\\bin\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 8811727,
      "reputation" : 349,
      "user_id" : 6584566,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/e641d474975f5e95a4bb282eb4b6e2ad?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "Asher A",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/6584566/asher-a"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 4,
    "last_activity_date" : 1477298741,
    "creation_date" : 1477298741,
    "answer_id" : 40214158,
    "question_id" : 4830253,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>It is in path/to/jdk/bin.\nMake sure that $JAVA_HOME is defined, and $JAVA_HOME/bin is added to $PATH, or else the 'keytool' command won't be recognized when called.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 14177576,
      "reputation" : 341,
      "user_id" : 12379280,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/c957264621fe2850df96c7fbf20a2f8c?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
